  <sect1 id="gnome-archive-introduction"> 
     <title>Introduction</title> 
     <para>
        <application>&app;</application> enables you to create archives from
        collections of files and folders. The applet creates gzip compressed archive
        files. 
     </para>
     <sect2 id="archive-generator-getstarted"> 
        <title>Getting Started</title> 
        <para>
          You can start <application>&app;</application> in the following ways: 
        </para>
        <variablelist> 
          <varlistentry> 
             <term>Applications menu</term> 
             <listitem> 
                <para>
                  Choose 
                  <menuchoice> 
                     <guimenu>System Tools</guimenu> 
                     <guimenuitem>Archive Generator</guimenuitem> 
                  </menuchoice>. 
                </para>
             </listitem> 
          </varlistentry> 
        </variablelist> 
        <variablelist> 
          <varlistentry> 
             <term>Command line</term> 
             <listitem> 
                <para>
                  Type 
                  <command>archive-generator</command> in a command line, then
                  press 
                  <keycap>Return</keycap>. 
                </para>
             </listitem> 
          </varlistentry> 
        </variablelist> 
        <figure id="archive-generator-start"> 
          <title> &app;</title> 
          <screenshot> 
             <mediaobject> 
                <imageobject><imagedata fileref="figures/archive-generator.png"
                  format="PNG"/> 
                </imageobject> 
                <textobject> 
                  <phrase>Screenshot of &app;. Shows menus: File, Edit, Help.Shows
                     Archive button. Shows status area.</phrase> 
                </textobject> 
             </mediaobject> 
          </screenshot> 
        </figure> 
     </sect2> 
     <sect2 id="archive-generator-whenstart"> 
        <title>When You Start &app;</title> 
        <para>
          When you start <application>&app;</application>, the following window
          is displayed. The window consists of the following elements: 
          <variablelist> 
             <varlistentry> 
                <term>Menubar</term> 
                <listitem> 
                  <para>
                     Contains standard menus. 
                  </para>
                </listitem> 
             </varlistentry> 
             <varlistentry> 
                <term>Archive collection area</term> 
                <listitem> 
                  <para>
                     You populate this area with pointers to files or folders to
                     create an archive collection. 
                  </para>
                </listitem> 
             </varlistentry> 
             <varlistentry> 
                <term>Archive button</term> 
                <listitem> 
                  <para>
                     You use the <guibutton>Archive</guibutton> button to create a gzip compressed file
                     when your archive collection is complete. 
                  </para>
                </listitem> 
             </varlistentry> 
             <varlistentry> 
                <term>Status area</term> 
                <listitem> 
                  <para>
                     The status area shows the number of files or folders that are
                     present in the current archive collection. 
                  </para>
                </listitem> 
             </varlistentry> 
          </variablelist> 
        </para>
     </sect2> 
  </sect1> 
  <sect1 id="gnome-archive-generator-usage"> 
     <title>Usage</title> 
     <sect2> 
        <title>To Create an Archive Collection</title> 
        <para>
          You can add files or folders to an archive collection in the following
          ways: 
          <variablelist> 
             <varlistentry> 
                <term>Drag pointers to files and folders from the Nautilus file manager.</term> 
                <listitem> 
                  <para>
                     Left-click and hold on the file or folder in the 
<application>Nautilus</application> file manager
                     window, then drag the cursor to the archive collection 
			area. Release the mouse button to create a pointer to the file 
or folder in the archive collection area. The file or folder remains in the original location. 
                  </para>
                </listitem> 
             </varlistentry> 
             <varlistentry> 
                <term>Select files and folders within
                  <application>&app;</application>.</term> 
                <listitem> 
                  <orderedlist> 
                     <listitem> 
                        <para>
                          Open the 
                          <guimenu>File</guimenu> menu, then choose 
                          <guimenuitem>Add file or folder</guimenuitem>. 
                        </para>
                     </listitem> 
                     <listitem> 
                        <para>
                          In the file selector dialog, select the files or folders
                          that you want to archive. 
                        </para>
                     </listitem> 
                     <listitem> 
                        <para>
                          Click OK to add pointers to files or folders in the archive
                          collection area. 
                        </para>
                     </listitem> 
                  </orderedlist> 
                </listitem> 
             </varlistentry> 
          </variablelist> 
          <figure id="archive-generator-contents"> 
             <title> &app; With Files Added</title> 
             <screenshot> 
                <mediaobject> 
                  <imageobject><imagedata
                     fileref="figures/archive-generator-contents.png" format="PNG"/> 
                  </imageobject> 
                  <textobject> 
                     <phrase>Screenshot of &app; main window with files
                        added.</phrase> 
                  </textobject> 
                </mediaobject> 
             </screenshot> 
          </figure> 
        </para>
     </sect2> 
     <sect2 id="gnome-archive-generator-remove"> 
        <title>To Remove Items From an Archive Collection</title> 
        <para>
          You can remove files or folders from an archive collection in the
          following ways: 
          <variablelist> 
             <varlistentry> 
                <term>Single file or folder</term> 
                <listitem> 
                  <orderedlist> 
                     <listitem> 
                        <para>
                          Select the single file or folder in the archive collection
                          area that you want to remove. 
                        </para>
                     </listitem> 
                     <listitem> 
                        <para>
                          Open the 
                          <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> menu, then choose 
                          <guimenuitem>Remove</guimenuitem>. 
                        </para>
                     </listitem> 
                  </orderedlist> 
                </listitem> 
             </varlistentry> 
             <varlistentry> 
                <term>Multiple files or folders</term> 
                <listitem> 
                  <para>
                     <orderedlist> 
                        <listitem> 
                          <para>
                             Open the 
                             <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> menu, then choose 
                             <guimenuitem>Select All</guimenuitem>. 
                          </para>
                        </listitem> 
                        <listitem> 
                          <para>
                             Deselect the files that you want to archive, then choose 
                             <guimenuitem>Remove</guimenuitem> from the 
                             <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> menu. 
                          </para>
                        </listitem> 
                     </orderedlist> 
                  </para>
                </listitem> 
             </varlistentry> 
             <varlistentry> 
                <term>All files and folders</term> 
                <listitem> 
                  <para>
                     Open the 
                     <guimenu>Edit</guimenu> menu, then choose 
                     <guimenuitem>Remove All</guimenuitem>. 
                  </para>
                </listitem> 
             </varlistentry> 
          </variablelist> 
        </para>
     </sect2> 
     <sect2 id="gnome-archive-generator-create"> 
        <title>To Save an Archive Collection</title> 
        <para>
          To save an archive collection as a gzip compressed file, click on the 
          <guibutton>Archive</guibutton> button, then use the 
          <guilabel>Save Results</guilabel> dialog to select a location and save
          the new archive. 
        </para>
        <para>
          To exit &app;, open the 
          <guimenu>File</guimenu> menu, then choose 
          <guimenuitem>Exit</guimenuitem>. 
        </para>
     </sect2> 
  </sect1> 
